Rearranging $x^2 - x - 1= 0$ give $x^2 = x + 1$.  So, repeatedly substituting $x+1$ for $x^2$ give us \begin{align*}
x^3 - 2x + 1 &= x(x^2)-2x + 1\\
&=x(x+1) - 2x + 1\\
&= x^2 + x -2x + 1\\
&= x^2 - x + 1\\
&= (x+1) - x + 1\\
&=\boxed{2}
\end{align*}

